Forward Chijoke Akuneto has been linked with a move to eight-time Nigeria Premier Football League champions, Enyimba. Akuneto was the top scorer in the NPFL last season, netting 19 times to help Rivers United win the title for the first time. The 25-year-old was spotted at the Enyimba Stadium on Sunday during Enyimbaâ€™s Abia State Federation Cup final win against Ahudiya FC. The striker is expected to put pen to paper on a deal with Enyimba in the coming days. The second half of the 2022/23 season will start on March 25. Enyimba will travel to Ibadan to face Shooting Stars on matchday 10.